<subSubSection id="EE2A739AF010DC9D0E19CBB70DF64532" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="0EA509C6A2992101132B63E51CC6F098" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F5F3B4BD5BA1CAB8BCBB022F3C7E3C0" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Shrubs 1-2 m tall, the branches erect to ascending; stems lacking spines. Leaves simple, sessile, in whorls at branch tips; blades lanceolate to oblanceolate, glabrous to glandular, usually appressed, the margins entire. Capitulescences of solitary, terminal heads, sessile. Capitula heterogamous, radiate or more rarely homogamous, discoid; involucres cylindrical to campanulate; receptacles plane, glabrous; phyllaries 5-7-seriate, lanceolate; ray florets 5-25, the corollas ligulate-bilabiate, the outer lip 4-nerved, tridentate, the inner lip bifid; styles cylindric, glabrous, bifid, the branches short, inconspicuous; disc florets 7-40, the corollas tubular, actinomorphic, glabrous, the limb deeply 
<pageBreakToken id="4C3102017B4CF9658367AA5CA54ACDEE" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" start="start">5</pageBreakToken>
-lobed, the lobes greater than 1/3 the length of the corolla, coiled; anthers linear, the terminal appendages lanceolate, fused into a column, truncate, the bases caudate; styles claviform, the branches short, rounded. Achenes glabrous or glandular-pubescent; pappus of scabrid bristles, isomorphic, yellowish. Chromosome number: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2195BFC9A88F0AF5294D48474427E98D" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BA895DE4A61404238FF8CEB881F05D37" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AFCD86DDF706CE14BD8023E40E1F8B28" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
All species are confined to the Andean Cordillera and associated inter-Andean valleys (
<figureCitation id="A1F88C904B9817969B9800BCE429E479" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution map of the currently recognized species of Plazia. The shaded area indicates high-elevation areas of the Andes above 3000 m. Locality data were obtained from Cabrera (1951), Ferreyra (1995), Missouri Botanical Garden (http: // www. tropicos. org /), Instituto de Botanica Darwinion (through http: // www. gbif. org /) and the herbaria ASU, B, F, HUT, P, SGO, US." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10579" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Two species are confinded to Peru; both are rare and only known from a few collection localities. Another species is restricted to the Andes of central Chile. 
<taxonomicName id="103A28AD8C7DDC42FE96B3679720DE0C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="daphanoides">
<emphasis id="F3FE7318489C0B37D605FCD3D086827B" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia daphanoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wedd. is the only wideranging species, being recorded from southern Peru and adjacent Argentina, Bolivia and Chile, usually in high-elevation, dry sites (
<bibRefCitation id="AE0A29BD602B03FD5DF4AB8D4FC879C4" author="Cabrera, AL" journalOrPublisher="Academic Press, London" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="B4" refString="Cabrera, AL, 1978. Flora de la Provincia de Jujuy. Compositae. Coleccion Cientifica del INTA, Buenos Aires, 1-726." title="Flora de la Provincia de Jujuy. Compositae. Coleccion Cientifica del INTA, Buenos Aires, 1 - 726." year="1978">Cabrera 1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6292AFCE10AD19BDB0D44094BF8E3945" author="Ferreyra, R" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Peruana de Botanica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="101 - 105" refId="B6" refString="Ferreyra, R, 1980. El genero Plazia en el Peru. Boletin de la Sociedad Peruana de Botanica 8: 101 - 105" title="El genero Plazia en el Peru." volume="8" year="1980">Ferreyra 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E33910E6046729ADB167831EB01B6D27" author="Ferreyra, R" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Peruana de Botanica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="B7" refString="Ferreyra, R, 1995. Family Asteraceae: Part VI, Tribe Mutiseae. In: MacbrideJF et al. Flora of Peru. Fieldiana Botany. N.S.35: 1-101." title="Family Asteraceae: Part VI, Tribe Mutiseae. In: MacbrideJF et al. Flora of Peru. Fieldiana Botany. N. S. 35: 1 - 101." year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C4E824953D4B4F6BB510EE88887F502D" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion.">
<paragraph id="2F355ADA1F8022BBD6BCD994B505CFD2" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EEE6B07D023F360F1E67BC7CBDF3FF50" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="A81D9A6270710732C9259B1396648C9E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8F8DD39746E27F9ED6A0C1DC475C81B3" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="52BA658FFC219C096BDE3C16A297E2C7" author="Ruiz Lopez, H" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="B20" refString="Ruiz Lopez, H, Pavon, JA, 1794. Florae Peruvianae, et Chilensis Prodromus. Madrid, 1-154." title="Florae Peruvianae, et Chilensis Prodromus. Madrid, 1 - 154." year="1794">
Ruiz 
<normalizedToken id="67CA344E2B3959F7074131CD939659EE" originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="809B2CBC1E2BFF9D6F30662770933F02" originalValue="Pavón">Pavon</normalizedToken>
(1794)
</bibRefCitation>
and they subsequently published its first species, 
<taxonomicName id="13A98A9E3801696283F2615CCA8D90F4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis id="DC2C26B6899DA7591FD5F5C82C324A62" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia conferta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ruiz &amp; Pav. (1798). All efforts at locating material corresponding to their type collection from Peru have not been successful (
<bibRefCitation id="47ED3672FADA10118596B25067F22349" author="Cabrera, AL" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="195 - 215" refId="B2" refString="Cabrera, AL, 1960. Notas sobre tipos de Compuestas Sudamericanas en herbarios Europeos. III, Los tipos de Ruiz y Pavon. Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica 8 (3-4): 195 - 215" title="Notas sobre tipos de Compuestas Sudamericanas en herbarios Europeos. III, Los tipos de Ruiz y Pavon." volume="8" year="1960">Cabrera 1960</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EAC81E2C10AB1FA249604FFF2A9A9D84" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<bibRefCitation id="08A2B9B2B2B496D33EB20AED5CA17C85" author="Weddell, HA" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.217" refId="B24" refString="Weddell, HA, 1855. Chloris Andina, vol 1. P.Bertrand, Paris, 1-231. ., 10.5962/bhl.title.217" title="Chloris Andina, vol 1. P. Bertrand, Paris, 1 - 231." url="10.5962/bhl.title.217" year="1855">Weddell (1855)</bibRefCitation>
provided an emended generic description for 
<taxonomicName id="962C4B0B83F3EDB8F07CE8BC56BC1AFA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3D9845898BFD117DB0CBDD347F1F4727" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and he recognized three species: 
<taxonomicName id="F13D8893460BFB00116FA2ED1F38F884" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis id="D5C0637EEF0320DDC1D951376A6E8591" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia conferta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ruiz &amp; Pav., 
<taxonomicName id="0E9CFF9D2424E470E29547F833663655" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cheiranthifolia">
<emphasis id="28AB4C0B1B9590BB14D2B2E65615F3AC" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia cheiranthifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(J. Remy) Wedd., and 
<taxonomicName id="C85AC02D0BCFEB83CB2ED5C1F2B2995F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="daphnoides">
<emphasis id="F8A52D5ECD1531433E0667C88193E558" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia daphnoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wedd. 
<bibRefCitation id="B876E302C552234B1FFC2D8F5F66B5C5" author="Reiche, C" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="735 - 738" refId="B18" refString="Reiche, C, 1905. Estudios criticos sobre la Flora de Chile. Anales de la Universidad de Chile 114: 735 - 738" title="Estudios criticos sobre la Flora de Chile." volume="114" year="1905">Reiche (1905)</bibRefCitation>
picked up the implied transfers by 
<bibRefCitation id="DE21ED156C59F7702F9D05B0034A3DD6" author="Hoffmann, O" editor="Engler, HGA" journalOrPublisher="Wilhelm Engelmann Verlag, Leipzig, 4 (5)" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="87 - 387" refId="B9" refString="Hoffmann, O, 1890-1894. Compositae. In: Engler, HGA, Prantl, KAE, Eds., Die natuerlichen Pflanzenfamilien. Wilhelm Engelmann Verlag, Leipzig, 4(5): 87 - 387" title="Compositae." volumeTitle="Die natuerlichen Pflanzenfamilien." year="1890 - 1894">Hoffmann (1890-1894)</bibRefCitation>
and treated 
<taxonomicName id="CD72DDD4B7CBEA001C9691C16EAC6EC8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5A92A8363A96B02A5D5BB20BA18D9B5E" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Chile as having three species: 
<taxonomicName id="8AF4A71F56811C3B5F9917853714CEC6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cheiranthifolia">
<emphasis id="74B95E8617C9F2D563A04E90965D8E49" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia cheiranthifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="65C81F22FE719FECE5A2FE1366CC3EA0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinifolia">
<emphasis id="E12ADD8EDFC84F54C794ABD3B6C70E7D" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plazia pinifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Phil.) O.Hoffm. [= 
